When giving clues, make sure to review all the words on the board, not just your team’s.

Clue rules
```
Invalid: The clue cannot be any of the words currently on the board. 
Invalid: The clue cannot use any part of a word on the board, such as saying "key" for "turkey". 
Invalid: The clue cannot be the number itself (e.g., "two" for "sea" and "animal"). 
Invalid: The clue cannot refer to the location of the words on the board, like "top 3". 
Invalid: Clues cannot be made-up names that aren't actual words or well-known proper names. 
Invalid: The clue cannot be the number of words to guess (e.g., saying "3" as a clue for "ball", "figure", and "octopus"). 
```
